            "last_activity_date": 1396533311,
            "creation_date": 1396533311,
            "body": "<p>You should look to <a href=\"http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/4.0.3.RELEASE/javadoc-api/org/springframework/transaction/TransactionStatus.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/4.0.3.RELEASE/javadoc-api/org/springframework/transaction/TransactionStatus.html<\/a> . \nIt has required functionality:\n- create savepoint\n- release savepoint\n- rollback to savepoint<\/p>\n\n<p>Of course, your transaction manager (and underlying JDBC driver, and DB) should support the functionality.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 22839943,
            "question_id": 22836854
        },
        {
